com.opengamma.strata.calc.runner

Class CalculationTask

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.opengamma.strata.calc.runner.CalculationTask

  • public final class CalculationTask
extends Object
    A single task that will be used to perform a calculation.

    This presents a uniform interface to the engine so all functions can be treated equally during execution. Without this class the engine would need to keep track of which functions to use for each input.

                                 CalculationFunction<? extends CalculationTarget> function,
                                 MarketDataMappings marketDataMappings,
                                 ReportingCurrency reportingCurrency)
        Obtains configuration for a task that will calculate a value for a target.

        This specifies the configuration of a single target, including the rules and cell index.

        Parameters:
        target - the target for which the value will be calculated
        measure - the measure being calculated
        rowIndex - the row index of the value in the results grid
        columnIndex - the column index of the value in the results grid
        function - the function that performs the calculation
        marketDataMappings - the mappings that specify the market data that should be used in the calculation
        reportingCurrency - the reporting currency
        Returns:
        the configuration for a task that will calculate the value of a measure for a target

      • execute

        public CalculationResults execute(CalculationEnvironment scenarioData,

        Executes the task, performing calculations for the target using multiple sets of market data.

        This invokes the function with the correct set of market data.

        Parameters:
        scenarioData - the market data used in the calculation
        refData - the reference data
        Returns:
        results of the calculation, one for every scenario in the market data
